MADLIB

Java properties file with variable replacement.

    Source: http://github.com/bigeasy/madlib/tree/master
    Wiki: http://wiki.github.com/bigeasy/madlib

    Issues and Tasks: http://github.com/bigeasy/madlib/issues

    License: The MIT License

    Contact: alan@blogometer.com

    Used-By:
        Java Cups:      http://github.com/bigeasy/cups
        Prattle:        http://github.com/bigeasy/prattle

PURPOSE

1. An implementation of a common Java properties file enhancement.
2. An implementation of a common variable subsitution pattern.

Used in properties files.

version: ${version}
configuration: ${user.home}/.config

Used in XML configuration files.

<angle-brackets>
    <version>${version}</version>
    <configuration>${user.home}/.config</configuration>
</angle-brackets>

Madlib can help you read Log4J, Ant or Maven configuration files.

MOTIVATION

This format is found in Log4J, Ant and Maven. I wanted a configuraiton file for
Prattle that was like Log4J. At the same time I needed a read Maven POM files.
